OL,3,CCouncil spending on transporting SEND
OL,4,Cpupils to school soars to #1.2 billion
OL,6,FCouncils have a legal obligation to
OL,7,Foffer free school transport in limited
OL,8,Fcircumstances, including if a school
OL,9,Fis more than three miles away or if a
OL,10,Fchild has special educational needs.
OL,12,FBut in recent years, growing demand
OL,13,Ffor SEND support has seen these
OL,14,Ftransport costs spiral. Data analysis
OL,15,Fshows that the number of SEND pupils
OL,16,Fbeing transported has risen from
OL,17,F51,415 to 61,934 across the three
OL,18,Fyears, with costs rising from #369
OL,19,Fmillion to #462 million.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/16
